title: 820-01958 charges the battery but won't power up
message: this board is charging the battery because it ramps up to 1.8 amps on the meter.  it will go into dfu and it will go through a revive but it never powers up at all.  pm_slp_sus_l is 3v . pm_slp_s5_l is 0v. is this a chipset issue?

title: 820-01958 charges the battery but won't power up
message:
Do you get SSD and G3S voltages?
If no important data, do DFU restore; many times, revive is not enough.

title: 820-01958 charges the battery but won't power up
message: i have another board that is the same model and it has 1.5 ohm resistance on ppbus.

title: 820-01958 charges the battery but won't power up
message:
That is pure short!
Remember to remove any power from the board and allow 10-15s before measuring diode mode, or ohm scale.

title: 820-01958 charges the battery but won't power up
message: i think that this board has an internal short. using the thermal cam, It get visibly warmest around r5600 when i inject voltage on ppbus. i've removed all components from that area and it still does the same.  I dont see a burn though
